window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>\"<b>Are you my mummy?\"</b></p> <p><b>Tessa Markham</b> returns home to find a child in her kitchen. He thinks she’s his mother. But Tessa doesn’t have any children.&nbsp;</p> <p><b>Not anymore.</b></p> <p>She doesn’t know who the little boy is or how he got there.</p> <p>After contacting the police, Tessa is suspected of taking the mystery child. Her whole life is turned upside down. And then her husband reveals a secret of his own….</p> <p>Tessa isn’t sure what to believe or who to trust. <b>Because someone is lying.</b> To find out who, she must confront her painful past. But is the truth more dangerous than Tessa realises?&nbsp;</p> <p><b>An absolutely pause-resisting psychological thriller with a twist that will make you wonder if you can ever trust anyone again. If you loved</b> <b><i>Gone Girl</i></b><b>,</b><b><i> The Girl on the Train</i></b><b>, and</b> <b><i>The Sister</i></b> <b>this book will have you hooked.</b>&nbsp;</p>"; 
